=beginObject#respond_to?(from ~/.rdoc)------------------------------------------------------------------------------  obj.respond_to?(symbol, include_private=false) -> true or false------------------------------------------------------------------------------Returns true if obj responds to the given method. Private methodsare included in the search only if the optional second parameter evaluates totrue.If the method is not implemented, as Process.fork on Windows, File.lchmod onGNU/Linux, etc., false is returned.If the method is not defined, respond_to_missing? method is called andthe result is returned.=end